The paper deals with the detection of fake followers on Twitter, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning classifiers, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of fake followers on society, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
